reviews.review_text: Great Chinese restaurant with very good BBQ items. We went here and got one of their set dinners that came with soup, lobster fried rice and 3 side dishes. We also got a set that came with Peking duck. The portions here were enormous and you will likely have leftovers if you dont go with many people. Overall I would come here again for their set dinners. Service was pretty good too considering how busy the storefront was.

Newer restaurant that replaced Peaceful restaurant that was there prior. The GOOD: place was busy for a Sat night at 8pm so thats a good sign. Didnt wait long for a table for 2. Pleasantly surprised at the preset 2x combo meats + main + soup + 2 bowls of white rice for $56. So we ordered BBQ duck + pork, main was green beans w minced pork & soup of the day. The MEH: menu should have spelled out that the combo soup is the soup of the day; no choosing. We asked for hot n sour, but the server brought the daily soup instead. When asked why, she then said the combo soup has to be daily soup. I found the BBQ pork and duck very tasty and not too oily. The green beans w minced pork were perfectly crispy but not too deep-fried. Again, very tasty. Didnt care for the daily soup, as its just a thin broth w few veggies + few pieces of meat. Would have preferred the hot n sour Final bill w tax was just under $60.
Really good, fresh legit Chinese food   good for Hong Konger taste buds. The servers are fast and friendly. Would come back!

On a busy evening, we got a table and the boss guy treated us very well.  There were a lot of customers eating but he came by to see how we were doing; a very nice and personable guy. The bbq Meats are great. Tables are a bit close to each - that would be  my only complaint

Amazing new Chinese BBQ restaurant. I came to dine-in with my family and got their 5 signature dishes menu which included: - House Special BBQ Platter (Roast Pork, BBQ Duck, Char Siu and Soy Sauce Chicken) - White Pepper Pork Tripe Soup - Lobster with Sticky Rice - Baked Codfish in Yuzu Mustard Sauce - Baked Beef Rib Their BBQ is all done very authentically. Roast pork is super crispy with a good mix of fat and meat. The skin on the BBQ duck is crisp and flavourful as well. If youve had their BBQ meat from the same restaurant in Richmond then you will know what to expect here, very high quality and delicious meats. Being a Chinese seafood restaurant as well, you can expect to order your traditional Chinese cuisine from here. What they also have sprinkled in are some slight fusion dishes that you will not find commonly elsewhere such as the baked codfish with yuzu mustard sauce and the baked beef rib. Their seafood is very fresh (both the lobster and codfish) and the beef rib is so amazingly tender. Definitely would recommend both those dishes. Overall very happy a new BBQ restaurant of this quality opened up in the neighbourhood. Service is very fast and friendly as well. Even though its their first days of opening, they already have line-ups for take-out BBQ. Will definitely come back more often and recommend this place to all who are in the area to check it out.
Really authentic Hong Kong style BBQ shop. We had lunch there, ordered a 3 BBQs on rice and steam veggies. Good service and they gave us free daily soup. The roasted pork was the best.
Love this place! Clean and good staff service. The bbq pork and roasted pork is so so good. Recommend you to try it!
Excellent food at good price. Really large portion and very Hong Kong style BBQ. Service is good for a Hong Kong restaurant.
Nice little shop with a good lunch selection.

Popped by to pick up some last minute dinner meat. Been meaning to check out, finally tried out. The half day and half skinny Char Siu ( aka BBQ PORK) cut was hands down the best Ive had in a long time. Better than Chinatown dollar meats,  TnT, and Richmond Master Hung. Id for back to try other items. The pic below shows Half of our 1lb $12.95/lb. The lady who served had an attitude/arrogance but the BBQ master was nice.

The roast pork is always crispy. The best around Burnaby and East Van, of all the places I tried. Prices of most dishes are good. The only thing is that like many small BBQ stores, they only have the belly part of the roast pork, not the whole pig. This makes it less authentic in my opinion, and you cant choose different cuts, such as the butt area where the meat is lean, albeit tougher.
Good food, BBQ duck and pork especially recommended
Food here is legit. They have great service. And phenomenal BBQ duck and Roasted Pork. Affordable pricing and it s good af.
The bbq is very well priced and delicious!  Wish there was a better line up process but overall the food is delicious!

My wife and I decided to try here since it took over Peaceful Restaurant. She was not impressed with the fact that we were the only couple (only staff was there). I told her to just enjoy the fact that all the attention will be towards us. The food brought back memories of the cooking that my mom cooked for me when I was a child. The salted duck egg with minced pork was almost as good (they should have mixed the egg into the pork) as what my mom made The BBQ hanging on the racks at the front has me wanting to go over and buy and take home in the near future. Im told that these guys were from the HK BBQ Master from Richmond and started their own business instead.

Do yourself a favor and visit this Chinese restaurant. The service is great, the food is great and the portion sizes are amazing. Absolutely the best meal we had while in. There are lots of Asian restaurants in Vancouver however this has got to be one of the top. BBQ is always a good option when going out to eat and this is not exception. The BBQ pork is so tender and flavourful and the roast pork is so crispy. Highly recommend!
My favorite place for BBQ meal. Parking: Can use the back lot for parking. Food : 5/5 |

Casual neighbourhood restaurant with delicious canton style dishes... steamed fresh lobster on rice is mouth-watering good... We loved their bbq meat platter with tasty duck, crispy roast pork, tender soy chicken and sweet roasted spare ribs... Popular local gem so make sure you make a reservation.
Excellent food, especially the barbecued and roasted meats.  You can tell they ve got a super hot wok back in kitchen locking in all the flavours to each dish.
Nice food at good price.  Perfect for family gatherings
Insanely delicious roasted pork! Crispy skin, juicy meat, tender fat. I d be happy having it for every special occasion.
Very crowded place to have dinner around 8pm...please make reservations...good food, lots to choose from, excellent services tendered...
The best in town for bbq pork
Deserves a 5 because traditional, Cantonese people would love this place. Not overly spiced or salted. Good texture of meats.
cheapest but good quality Cantonese BBQ meats platter
The food is 6 stars. The rest need to be upgraded.
It is like little Honk Kong. Delicious food and excellent customer service. Expensive for me. Wheelchair accessible, bus routes steps away 26, 41,19
Reasonable price but food portion is big. food taste good and fast. In general is good deal and taste good, sitting is not that good, worth to come again
Great service . You will be served dessert after the meal. The food is great too. Highly recommend.
Good food, good BBQ food, traditional Cantonese food.
Their bbq are consistently done right
Great food for a good price. I definitely recomend.
Love their roasted pork.
Amazing bbq pork!!!
Like their BBQ pork
The taste is very good and worth recommending. My whole family loves their roast duck and fried chicken. Other side dishes are also very good. The service is also very friendly.
Pre-order, fresh! Delicious! Cook it in a big steamer, clean your hands and feet without washing yourself, you can eat 3 meals

It s really great, and the price is very affordable. I used to eat this roast pork often in Richmond. Maybe because of the new store, the waiter is not very familiar with the business. But it doesn t affect the deliciousness of the food.

Barbecued rice, fried noodles, and even Japanese dishes and fresh seafood are all available. The service attitude is amiable and friendly and answers questions. It is mainly a neighborhood business. The price is reasonable and it is worth trying.

The roasted pork is really delicious, the roasted pork is crispy on the outside and tender on the inside   The lobster rice is on point    The side dishes are huge. Will definitely visit again next time!
I ate with my girlfriends family after helping her parents move. The lobster rice was 10/10. I will definitely come here again.
Very authentic barbecue. It s been a long time since I ve had such delicious Cantonese food! My friend recommended this lobster rice, it s really good.
The roasted duck is charred on the outside and tender on the inside, the skin of the roasted pork is crispy and the meat is soft, delicious
Its big and delicious, and the price is affordable!
Authentic Cantonese barbecue food
Top notch barbecued pork!

Cantonese BBQ Seafood opened up in the former Peaceful location on Kingsway. The little mini mall has a busy parking lot but you can usually find street parking (both free and paid). Weve been here a few times to grab a quick bbq lunch combo. But we finally visited for dine-in recently. In addition to their bbq service, they have a full Chinese seafood menu offering. We ordered the 3 item bbq combo (you pick and choose which bbq items you want but we opted for the roast pork, bbq, and soya sauce chicken). While the bbq price is higher than the lunch combos, you get more meat. Not a bad price when you consider how much the price of bbq duck has gone up lately. The duck was good... meaty and juicy. Roast pork has nice crispy skin. A welcome addition to the area for bbq. Pea tips were good too. And I like that we received complimentary soup to start and green bean soup for dessert. Really want to come back here and try some of their seafood combos. Update: We did return in October to try a dinner combo with a 2lb lobster sticky rice with 2 bbq items plus 1 other dish for $118 (we picked the sole fillets with veggies). We also added the Taiwanese cauliflower with lap cheung and bacon. Again, you get complimentary soup and dessert. Bbq items were as good as before.

Its what you call Asian Fast Food.  Very fast and efficient.  Great bang for your money these days when eating out.  Portion size is plenty compared to other places.  As always some dishes were definitely better than others.  Stick to what they are known for and you cant go wrong.

Visited 2 weeks ago on a weekday, not very busy, not quiet, just easy to get a table for 2. Ordered 2 entries and it comes with soup of the day and dessert for free. Good quality food for the money! Definitely come back again and try something else on the menu Parking: Lots of parking behind the restaurant from London Drugs lot, free.
The food quality is above average. The price is reasonable. Variety could have been better though. I would recommend this place if you want to try some typical and authentic Cantonese food.
One of the few places that offered a BBQ meats counter. Pretty decent and will definitely go back to try other dishes.

Newly opened Cantonese BBQ restaurant on Kingsway busy Joyce area. Limited parkings. Busy and central location. Food was good. Came out quickly and hot. BBQ pork was very tasty and juicy. Yet very crunchy skin. We ordered double items plate. Half duck half BBQ pork. Duck was good too. Deep fried squid wasnt as crunchy as it should be. Beef green beans was heavily sauced and load of black beans. Over powering the whole dish.  Lastly, eggplant tofu scallops. Good amount of scallops and tasted fresh. Tofu was freshly deep fried before cooking into pot. Very few eggplant.  Tasted a bit too sweet than savory.  Overall a little bit too salty. I will ask for less salt next visit. Service was good and fast. They were very busy. Yet they were able to take care of the basic needs. Polite and friendly. Overall, it is a great addition for this area for Cantonese cuisine. We have enough hot pot or skewers restaurants in this area.

Really solid spot for Cantonese eats! Portions are huge. Appreciated the free soup during lunch. We got the bbq duck and roasted pork with noodles for lunch, as well as a beef chow fun noodles. Prices were reasonable too.

Found this little gem just across from one of our go to spots on Kingsway. We ordered bbq roast pork, deep fried tofu, fried rice and a side of Chinese broccoli. The table menu, take out counter menu and the delicious crunchy roast pork was very similar to HK BBQ Master in Richmond. As it turns out, it is owned by the same person, mentioned by our server. So if you don t want to line up and wait for a table or do take out at HK BBQ Master this the place for you.

Although the restaurant appeared to be small and not fancy decorated, the barbecue food is famous at this place, and dishes is good size to fill your stomach. my best choice of food is barbecue ribs, barbecue pork with crunch skin and half fat CharSiu, tender meats and honey sauce that is so delicious. Parking at the back large parking lot but full all the time.
Good food and service. Today maybe no AC, the front door was open
The roasted meat platter is amazing. The roasted pork was juicy and the skin was so crispy - like a fresh bag of Lays! Portions are big - good value for money. Food
Very flavourful food, and overall good quality.

Super busy, often long line up.  So popular, they ran out of most BBQ meats by 7pm.  Understandably, the roast bbq pork was the best. There are vegetarian options, limited but also very tasty. Downside: packed, long wait for food and service.  Hard to find parking.
Price is reasonable. Their Cantonese style chow mien is one of the best in town. It is lightly fried to just the right crispiness that is not easy to achieve.

The pork intestine pepper soup is thick and full of flavor. BBQ meats are nicely done. The ginger chicken rice had a nice flavor but the rice was cold. The waitress was friendly and efficient. The dining area is bright but as with all typical Chinese restaurants, the decoration is dated and can be noisy.

I ve been here a few times now. BBQ duck, chicken and pork is solid. The tea on the table is great. Service is pleasant and atmosphere is cozy. I ve had a few dishes off the menu and they have come out way too salty, over cooked, flavours are drowned out and slow to arrive at the table. I guess it s just a matter of what you order and who is cheffing it up in the back? I give it a 4 star because I want people coming in and keeping the place busy.
We got there late and limited choices of BBQ  items.  They are out of duck.  The Chinese soup is quite alright.  We will go back again
Decent food, specialty of course is the various Cantonese BBQ meat and boiled chicken.  But the quality is inconsistent, sometimes its quite good and sometimes the meat can be dry.
This place has one of the best Chinese BBQ meats in town. The staff are quite friendly and portions are nice and big.
Good BBQ stuff not bad at all
Traditional Cantonese food, the bbq pork and roasted pork are very good.  Definitely would eat here again.
Great BBQ place.  Pricing is reasonable and quality is above average.
Came for lunch, all the dishes came out great and piping hot.  Prices avg or better than avg.  Would def come again!  BBQ items were great.
This place is actually one of the better barbecue places a little bit on the pricier side but worth it
New Cantonese BBQ style restaurant in East Vancouver area. Most of the dinner dishes were good but their main specialty , the BBQ items were just average and mediocre at best. Good service.
Very good cooking and tasty , people are nice , just the parking and traffic in the whole area is terrible
